Parameters Configuration Screen

Parameter configuration screen is used for creating alerts, enlighten the system to any ad-hoc information, putting constraints on specified levels of product or store and creating exceptions. It is a useful screen for our customers to have control over the algorithm.

You can reach the screen by following the path Inventory Planning ‚Üí Target Parameter Configuration.

When user clicks on the menu item, there will be three tabs at the upper part of the screen.

1. Parameter Adjustments
2. Adjustment Detail
3. Create New Adjustment

On the upper left corner of the Parameter Adjustments screen, there are 3 icons next to Actions button.

The first button helps refreshing the data on the page. To find your saved filters, use Filters icon next to refresh icon. From the eye shaped button, you can filter the data by columns.

At the bottom of the screen, there are pagination section and a drop-down menu that helps user to customize row count per page.

- The Actions column helps user to delete a parameter set. Once user clicks on the bin icon and Yes respectively, the parameter set got deleted.
- The Adjustment ID column is unique to each ruleset and clickable. When user clicks it, it opens up a page where user can edit and see the details of the parameter set.
- The Status column is binary. If a rule is active, it can be switched to passive. If a rule is passive and not expired, the button can be switched to active. The rule then activates simultaneously.
- The Solution Type column is what user selected as solution type when defining the rule. It is not adjustable.
- The Adjustment Type column is what user selected as adjustment type when defining the rule. It is not adjustable.
- The Scope column is what user selected as scope type when defining the rule. It is not adjustable
- The Start Date column is the minimum date of child items of a set. In other words it shows the minimum date the rule initiates.

e minimum date of child items of a set. In other words it shows the minimum date the rule initiates.
- The End Date column is the maximum date of child items of a set. In other words it shows the maximum date the rule terminates.
- The Remaining Days column gives users how much time left to end of the rule. If the rule is passive, the color of the icon is grey, if active, the color is green. If the rule will last forever, the column value is ‚ÄúUnlimited‚Äù
- The Description column is the description of a parameter given by the user when initially set. It is editable.
- The User Name column tells users who put the rule.
- The Created At column defines the creation date.
- The Updated At column defines the last update date.

Activating, passivating or deleting a defined parameter set

At column defines the last update date.

Activating, passivating or deleting a defined parameter set

1. User can select one or multiple rows by clicking the boxes stand on the left side of each row.
2. Selected rows' colors changes and Action button on the right upper corner is activated. Watch out that expired rules‚Äô boxes can not be checked.
3. User can activate, passivate delete the rules selected by using the Action button

When user clicks on the Adjustment ID of a row, Adjustment Detail Tab opens up.

Adjustment Detail Tab

User can switch between Adjustment IDs to make changes on selected options. The description field is also editable on the tab. Users can alter the rule by defining new items to the set or deleting some. Besides user can edit via uploading an excel.

Things to be taken into consideration:

1. Start date cannot be earlier than the end date.
2. User can only add same group level item to an existing rule. If, for example a product group has been selected, the ‚ÄúAdd New‚Äù button is only functional for product groups.
3. User can deactivate or edit any rule that is currently up-to-date. When the activation date of a parameter is passed, the rule is automatically deactivated and editing is blocked. If a rule is wanted to be reactivated, user can create a new parameter.
4. While parameters can be defined for a certain period of time, the user can also make the parameter rule last forever by not setting an end date, if desired.
5. If an item is defined in multiple rules, the rule that is added most recently and not-expired is applied.
6. Beware the input value is integer and between valid interval. If you want to input float values, contact with your project responsible.

Control Tower

Control tower shows a detailed summary of services where you will be able to track the performances. It is mainly used in order to see the important daily statistics, sales performance, KPI performances & trend changes in one page for easier analysis.

The page has several attributes. All attributes can be minimized by the icon on session‚Äôs upper right corner.

1. Daily Order Statistics

Here you can find your daily statistics of orders from Suppliers to Distribution Centers, Suppliers to Stores directly, and Distribution Centers to Stores along with overall total Store Inventory data with Upcoming, Landing & Delayed POs.

Next to blue rectangles, there are arrows that goes to Store Replenishment Screens once clicked. When the screen opens up, you will see the data is filtered according to the arrow‚Äôs description you selected.

1. Sales, Inventory & Order History

is filtered according to the arrow‚Äôs description you selected.

1. Sales, Inventory & Order History

In this graph, you can see your sales, inventory & forecasts from this year. Also, you can add the last year's data for comparison just by selecting the box "Show Last Year".

If you want to change the outfit of the graph, you can always edit it from the "Settings" on the upper right corner.¬†If you need more detailed information, you can always check the details from "Go To Report" page.

1. KPI Overview

In the KPI Overview session, some quick KPI components are shown. These are:

- Availability Ratio: Shows the filtered item group‚Äôs availability rate
- Lost Sales Ratio: Shows the filtered item group‚Äôs lost sales ratio
- Weeks of supply: Displays the remaining WOS of selected group of items in selected locations.

You can find the details for each of these KPI's from the "Show Report" section below them.

1. Sales Trend Changes

e details for each of these KPI's from the "Show Report" section below them.

1. Sales Trend Changes

By looking at the sales through the details of stores, categories & products, you can analyze your sales performance for the last 4 weeks in detailed.

If you would like to check out how are the sales going regarding to the related forecasts, you can click on the "Go To Forecast" page from upper right corner.

1. Promotions & Special Days

In this section, you will observe upcoming promotions or special days related to your products. This way, you will have a chance to be more prepared, and will be more informed about the future forecasts & their reasoning. You can check out the ‚ÄúAll Planned Promotions‚Äù page in order to see upcoming events, add new events, or edit the existing ones.

1. Alerts Review

‚Äù page in order to see upcoming events, add new events, or edit the existing ones.

1. Alerts Review

In this section, you will see the alerts related to your data. . This section will only show the related day‚Äôs top critical alerts. Click All Alerts & Exceptions link below to visit all alerts and exceptions. For more information please visit the help page of related screen.

1. Filters

Click on funnel icon on the upper left corner. There, you can select a filter as you wish and save it for future from Save As, or edit the saved filter from Update. When you select a saved filter, you can see a new icon Delete pops up. You can use delete to eliminate saved filter or use reset to go back to initial filter interface. Once you click Reset, the saved filters don‚Äôt get wiped away.

o go back to initial filter interface. Once you click Reset, the saved filters don‚Äôt get wiped away.

You can also make the filter your default one. Once the box is checked, every time you visit the page, the filter is applied automatically. Remember, these saved filters and default one are only visible to you, not to other person in your organization.

From the currency part next to filter, you can change the currency type.

You can access to different store types from the session next to currency. "All", "Brick and Mortar Only", "Brick and Mortar with Omni", and "Online Only" are selectable. Besides user can choose to see ‚ÄúOnly new products‚Äù or ‚ÄúOnly new stores‚Äù by clicking on the related boxes.

Alerts

Alert screen is used for showing the alerts defined and allow user to solve the errors in the pipeline.

rt screen is used for showing the alerts defined and allow user to solve the errors in the pipeline.

In the Alerts Review page, you will see the alerts with their related columns of Priority, ID, Description, Status, Item, Destination, Item and Destination Info icon, Current Value, Reference Value, Alert Date & Actions. This way, you will be able to analyze the alerts in detail and make the necessary edits by going to the directed screen by clicking on the yellow arrow icon of the alert record. Once you click on the yellow arrow icon, you will be directed to a new page where you can make your controls & analysis.

From the menu on the left of the page, you can filter the alerts by date, type and category. Once you click on the green ‚ÄúApply Filter‚Äù button, the filter will be applied to all alerts data.

Also, you can filter the alerts by their priority levels (Critical, High, Medium, Resolved & Pending) from the options above the data.

their priority levels (Critical, High, Medium, Resolved & Pending) from the options above the data.

Below some column names, there is also filtering options you can use. You can, for instance, go to Status column and filter for only Pending ones if you want. Some filters allow you to search with characters. You can search by the starts with, contains, ends, equals and not equals options.

If you are satisfied with what alert is indicating, click on the green thick to save the alert as resolved. If you want to resolve multiple rows, select at least on row. The Resolve button will be activated.

There are 4 status of orders:

1. Order Guardrail - an alert is detected
2. Order Received - order has no alert and received a suggested order quantity successfully.
3. Out of Frequency - the pair is not in scope
4. Order Reviewed - the order is reviewed by user and ready to approve

Forecast Review & EditForecast Review:

Forecast Review and Edit screen is used in order to understand the reasoning behind the replenishment plans & predict the future sales performance better. This page does not include store-based dimensions as it is only limited to product groups for better performance of the related calculations.

In this page, you will be able to see the forecasts, sales quantity & store inventory in time series graph. This page will show you high-level, product group based forecast metrics and provide accuracy controls. You will see two different graphs:

1. Aggregate Chart: Shows forecasts, sales quantities, and store inventory in a time series. This will help you analyze the chosen product according to the chosen metrics in a graph.

me series. This will help you analyze the chosen product according to the chosen metrics in a graph.

1. Breakdown Chart: Shows the analysis of the product group that is chosen from the grid with the metrics. If you see a problem in your data, you will be able to detect the problematic product sub-groups easily by using this chart.

By clicking the ‚ÄúSettings‚Äù button on the upper right corner of the graph, you can edit the appearance of the graph by choosing whether you would like to see as line, bar or secondary axis for each of the attributes. Also, you can filter the data you want to see from the filters on the upper left corner of the graph.

lso, you can filter the data you want to see from the filters on the upper left corner of the graph.

Under the graph, you will see the data as a table. Here, you can use the grid attribute which will enable to drilldown and analyze the aggregations from their sub-hierarchies if you have chosen more than one hierarchy (you can choose 3 hierarchies max). If you use the grid setting, you will be able to analyze your total data from the graph, and break it down into hierarchies and analyze each one individually from the grid.

You can specify the hierarchies from the ‚ÄúAggregations‚Äù option. Also, you can choose the specific units from ‚ÄúQuantity‚Äù option, and filter the shown data as only promo, only non-promo, or both from the ‚ÄúShow Total‚Äù filters.

Default metrics of this page are Sales, Revenue, and Inventory. You can add different metrics to this graph such as Revenue, Warehouse Inventory, Product Count, Store Count and Pair Count from the ‚ÄúMetrics‚Äù option. These metrics that are shown can be hidden/shown according to the customer requirements. Also, keep in mind that you may need Product, Store, and Pair Count metrics as they are useful when it comes to analyzing sales and forecasts. The counts are calculated from forecast data and helps the user to explain the forecast amounts relative to the pair/product/store counts. The sales quantity metric is calculated the daily data of the client, regarding the hierarchies. Since the pairs are not joined in this calculation, the category‚Äôs sales total can be observed here. This helps the user to understand the historic categorical sales and forecast scope total.
